A non-Governmental Organisation (NGO), Grooming People for Better Livelihood Centre, will on Saturday, April 16, 2019 hold its ninth yearly splash raffle draw promo in Ejigbo, Lagos. The event will feature rewarding of 386 clients with gift items ranging from 24 Keke Napep tricycles, 58 deep freezers, 140 double-door fridges and 164 – 5KVA/2.5KVA power generating sets. In an interview with The Guardian, Chief Executive Officer of the Centre, Dr. Godwin Nwabunka, said the yearly event was simply a means of saying “Thank You” to the Centre’s numerous clients, particularly for their unalloyed loyalty and patronage. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .